Last couple days of practice were really hard for me, and so I tried doing different things; I went on a long walk, I layed down on my yoga mat (sometimes for a couple hours on end, next to my salt lamp) and just found ways to feel supported. 

I also went back to read my comments on the last 30 Days Of Yoga to see how I felt around this time; not realizing that I inadvertently created a Yoga journal (that I ended up sharing with you and the world lol) and I felt then how I felt now! So I realized maybe I should keep a Yoga Journal to see my thoughts more clearly: where they repeat and how they change. I also noticed that there have been so many thoughts I haven't been sharing because not all of them are positive (towards myself) or a bit repetitive and so I've been keeping them inside, not realizing that maybe keeping them inside is probably what's causing them to manifest as energy  blockages. I'm not really sure to be honest.

I'm trying to lose weight for the last year, and eating food I do not like, trying to work out. The problem is I have depression problem for my whole life, I have the lack of endotrophin receptors. Meaning that the myth of coming out of the workout happy and fulfilled and all that crap is just a myth for me. I get out of a workout tired and often as not a sobbing mess, because the chemicals start flowing, and unfortunately I get the short end of the happy ones, while the other ones just make me feel shitty.
Spring is here and everybody is talking about working out, and I should, but I am scared shitless going through that again (been in hardcore training few years back, I lost weight, but I cried all the time, meds or not). 
I reached the weight platou 2 mths ago (before I lost 4kg in a month), and it's not moving ANYWHERE. And I'm losing hope here. I need to lose 10 more kilos. 
Yoga is basically the only thing I've discovered so far, that keeps me in control of my mind while 'working out' most of the time. Not today, though. Hopefully, I will calm down.

29 days! Wow! Never thought I could make it this far... It's been a wonderful self-discovery journey! I have to confess that when I read your email about this practice I felt a bit worried because I said to myself "No way I can pull this off!" I mean, how many times have I said to myself I Love Myself? But for some reason, the moment I stepped on to the mat I started repeating in my head all the things I loved until there was nothing else to love but me... This was it! This was the unevitable challenge! There wasn't any choice left but repeating I Love myself even if I didn't resonate with it¬†at all...Adriene, this is not stupid at all. If there's people who believe it, it's because they're just hiding behind words and prejudice and because it seems easier to accept this mindset. I mean, "it's better the devil you know than the devil you don't", right?Anyway, this experience was the hardest and the most rewarding I've had so far. At the end I could feel how my body responded to the mantra I Love myself. Thank you so much for your guidence.Namaste :D

Thank you so much for this experience.  I realized my need to start shifting my self talk back in November and found your channel and the 30 days of yoga videos that you did last year.  I followed through with all 30 videos and about 20 days in realized how much I just wanted to go home every day and do yoga.  Physically, I felt amazing and so in harmony with my body, but I felt that there was a mental component missing.  I was still harbouring some negative self talk in my mind and I wasn't happy with that. 
These Yoga Camp videos have changed my life.  The daily mantras have enabled me to focus on what I am truly grateful for in my life and shift my way of thinking about myself.  I can honestly say I am much more happy in general than when I started out.  I can now also honestly say that I love myself and that has never before been true in my life.  A few of the mantras did indeed bring tears to my eyes but those were the ones that meant the most.  
I am endlessly thankful, +Yoga With Adriene!  #YOGACAMP
